-- Dortmund Opens 10-Point Lead in German Soccer; Juventus Wins 3-1 in Italy
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-12-06T00:53:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-05/dortmund-opens-10-point-lead-in-german-soccer-villarreal-wins-in-spain.html
Borussia Dortmund extended its lead
in German soccer’s Bundesliga to 10 points with a 2-0 victory
at Nuremberg.  Mats Hummels opened the scoring in the 23rd minute
yesterday and Robert Lewandowski got the second goal two
minutes from the end. Dortmund has won 13 of its 15 league
games, with one draw and a loss.  Second-placed Mainz, on 30 points, lost 2-1 at Eintracht
Frankfurt two days ago. Bayer Leverkusen had a 3-2 win over
Cologne yesterday to overtake Hanover and go a point behind
Mainz. Defending champion Bayern Munich is seventh after a 2-0
loss at Schalke.  AC Milan leads Italy’s Serie A on 33 points after beating
Brescia 3-0 two days ago. Lazio is three points behind in
second after inflicting a fourth loss of the season on
defending champion Inter Milan, which is now in sixth place.  Third-place Juventus is six points off the lead after
beating Catania 3-1 last night. Sampdoria defeated Bari 3-0
earlier yesterday to join Inter, Palermo and Roma on 23 points.  Barcelona still leads the Spanish standings after a 3-0
win at Osasuna two days ago, with second-placed Real Madrid two
points behind after a 2-0 victory over Valencia. Villarreal, in
third, has 30 points after a 1-0 win over Sevilla.  Lille went top of the French standings after a 6-3 win
over Lorient yesterday. Paris Saint-Germain and Rennes are a
point behind and Marseille is a further point back after a 1-0
injury-time loss at Nice.  In the Netherlands, PSV Eindhoven, a 5-2 winner over
Heracles Almelo yesterday, leads on goal difference from FC
Twente, which beat De Graafschap 2-0.  WEEKEND RESULTS
===============
Italy: Lazio 3-1 Inter Milan; Chievo 2-2 Roma; AC Milan 3-0
Brescia; Cesena 0-2 Bologna; Sampdoria 3-0 Bari; Parma 2-1
Udinese; Lecce 1-3 Genoa; Fiorentina 1-0 Cagliari; Catania 1-3
Juventus. Dec. 6: Napoli v Palermo.  Spain: Levante 2-0 Atletico Madrid; Osasuna 0-3 Barcelona; Real
Madrid 2-0 Valencia; Espanyol 1-0 Sporting Gijon; Malaga 4-1
Racing Santander; Getafe 3-0 Real Mallorca; Almeria 1-1 Real
Zaragoza; Villarreal 1-0 Sevilla; Real Sociedad 2-0 Athletic
Bilbao. Dec. 6: Deportivo La Coruna v Hercules.  Germany: St. Pauli 1-0 Kaiserslautern; Borussia
Moenchengladbach 1-2 Hanover; Wolfsburg 0-0 Werder Bremen;
